  "notes": "Murcian Spanish (Panocho/Murciano). Transitional between Castilian and Andalusian: shares coda aspiration, -d deletion, yeísmo, and liquid neutralisation with Andalusian. Some traces of Aragonese/Catalan substrate from medieval settlement (vowel harmony traces). Mixed distinción/seseo zones.",
